rComments: One of the bests professors I've ever had. He has a quirky sense of humor and explains things really well. Told us exactly what to study for tests too.
One of the best profs at U of T

King is an organized and charismatic lecturer (with nice British accent!) You realize when you prepare for exams that all his materials/ideas actually connect to overarching themes. When approached, he is very nice and shows much care.

I second all the comments about him as a good speaker, very clear and organized in his lectures but he's also a great teacher too. He's approachable, respectful and so knowledgeable.  Sweet and funny as well.
Rob King is fantastic. His lectures will captivate you with clarity, humour and a serious sense of his passion for the subject.

Rob King is an excellent professor. He's polite, intelligent, organized, well-rounded, and has quite the sense of humor. His tests are challenging but fair, and as long as you do the required readings it's quite possible to get a very good grade. Not just the ladies will enjoy this course ;)

Great speaker, well organized clear lectures, and prepares you INCREDIBLY well for an exam. Not an essay prof. per say, but one who gives you the tools to be a succesful student in his class. Highly recommended. Many other profs could learn from him.

Rob King is a great lecturer, he's funny and well versed in his subjects. I've really enjoyed taking his classes and would definitely take virtually any other class he teaches. King is a fantastic speaker and makes his lectures fun to attend and learn from.
